			<h1>Location</h1>
			<p>The "Location" header refers to a resource that has some relationship to the request, typically a URI to be followed for a redirect.</p>

			<h2>Overview table</h2>
			<dl class="inline">
				<dt>Name</dt>
				<dd property="w:HTTP-Header-name">Location</dd>
				<dt>Direction</dt>
				<dd property="w:HTTP-Header-direction">Response</dd>
				<dt>Description</dt>
				<dd property="w:HTTP-Header-description">Refers to another resource, depending on status code</dd>
				<dt>Specification</dt>
				<dd property="w:specification"><a href="http://httpwg.org/specs/rfc7231.html#header.location">RFC 7231: HTTP/1.1 Semantics and Content &#xA7;7.1.2. Location</a></dd>
			</dl>

			<h2>Syntax</h2>
			<pre class="abnf-definition">Location = URI-reference</pre>

		</main>
